Install

   pwntooth

1. Run "make" to compile binary.
2. Run "make install" to install into system.
3. Run "make clean" to delete binary from pwntooth directory.
4. Edit pwntooth.conf for specified attacks.  It can be found in "/etc/bluetooth/".


   addition tools

I provided the addition tools used by pwntooth.  Feel free to download tools from their origional sources and/or update tools.

1. "cd" to "tools" directory.
2. Run "make" to compile binaries.
3. Run "make install" to install into system.
4. Run "make clean" to delete binaries directory.